  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You extend your hand towards one creature you can see within range, constricting the air around its throat and forcing the creature to make a <strong>Strength saving throw</strong>. On a failed save, the creature takes <strong>3d6 bludgeoning damage</strong>, is immobilized, and cannot breathe for the spell's duration. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage, and the spell ends. A choking target repeats the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the spell on a success.</p><p>As an action while the spell lasts, you deal <strong>2d6 bludgeoning damage</strong> to the target.</p><p><strong><em>At Higher Levels:</em></strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, both the initial damage and the successive damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 2nd, and you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 2nd.</p>",
